cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.DS 

This paper deals with Conditional Random Fields (CRFs) applied to sequence tagging problems, which are commonly studied in the fields of machine learning (cs.LG), natural language processing (cs.CL), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also presents algorithms for computing the partition function, marginals, and MAP, which are fundamental problems in computational complexity theory (cs.CR) and data structures (cs.DS).
